<!-- üìò AO Strategy Description -->
<section>
  <h2>üìò Strategy Description</h2>

  <p>This EA uses the <strong>Awesome Oscillator (AO)</strong> across 3 selectable timeframes (HTF, ITF, ETF) to determine momentum alignment and confirm trade direction. You can independently enable any timeframe as a filter to confirm trend consistency. 
  AO bar color is used as the primary signal: <strong>green bars</strong> indicate bullish momentum, and <strong>red bars</strong> indicate bearish momentum.</p>

  <p>For example, if AO is green on H4 and H1, and Entry Timeframe is M15, a Buy trade will only be taken when M15 also turns green. 
  The Exit Timeframe governs when the trade is closed (e.g., a red AO bar on Exit TF signals an exit).</p>

  <div class="highlight">
    <p><strong>Entry Timeframe (Dropdown):</strong> HTF / ITF / ETF</p>
    <p><strong>Exit Timeframe (Dropdown):</strong> HTF / ITF / ETF</p>
  </div>

  <h3>‚úÖ Entry Conditions:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Buy:</strong> AO bar is green on selected Entry Timeframe and (if selected) also green on H1 and H4.</li>
    <li><strong>Sell:</strong> AO bar is red on selected Entry Timeframe and (if selected) also red on H1 and H4.</li>
    <li>If Exit Timeframe is set to H4, the trade won‚Äôt close until AO turns opposite on H4.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>‚úÖ Optional Filters:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>ADX Filter:</strong> If enabled, requires:
      <ul>
        <li>ADX value &gt; 25</li>
        <li>+DI &gt; -DI (for Buy) or -DI &gt; +DI (for Sell)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>MA Filter (EMA/SMA):</strong> If enabled, confirms price position:
      <ul>
        <li>Buy: Price above MA</li>
        <li>Sell: Price below MA</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Both filters (ADX and MA) can be enabled individually or together and will apply on the selected Entry Timeframe or as configured per strategy design.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>üîÅ Manual Trade Handling:</h3>
  <p>If a trade is manually closed, the EA will wait for a new valid signal to re-enter. This prevents instant re-entries and avoids repeated entries due to temporary volatility.</p>
</section>

